The Kano State Government has suspended the operational licences of all private schools in the state. The State Commissioner for Education, Sanusi Kiru, stated this at a press conference in Kano On Monday. The decision was sequel to the murder of a five-year old school pupil, Hanifa Abubakar, by her teacher an proprietor of private school she attended, Abdulmalik Tanko. LEADERSHIP earlier reported the arraignment of Tanko and two accomplices before a Magistrate Court in the state on Monday. On the suspension of the operational licences for private schools in the State, Kiru said the state government will set up a special committee for guidance on the next course of action. Details Laterâ€¦